Position Summary

The Data Analyst is a professional position supporting the Agency Performance, Program Integrity, and Innovation Department in our project to prepare the DOL to procure products and services for an Enterprise Licensing and Permitting technology platform modernization. The Data Analyst is responsible for related data planning and the functionality therein that supports the business, which will mainly encompass the effort to cleanse, transform and model data with the goal of discovering and presenting useful information, informing conclusions, and supporting decision-making in the platform modernization project. The Data Analyst will assist the Project Manager in coordinating project activities, alerting the PM and team of out of scope activities. The Data Analyst will assist in developing Project Plan (Charter) and Statement of Work (SOW) and gain approvals. Responsibilities: The Data Analyst investigates, documents, and offers solutions to data collection and data quality problems, including functional requirements, needed workflows, and accompanying data plans to improvements, close gaps, and to support the development of new applications and workflows within our technology environments. As such he/she must be versatile, a quick learner, and an excellent communicator and translator to understand and clearly express these concepts to the stakeholders involved. This position must be able to communicate to both technical and non-technical staff and to translate concepts between those groups. Insufficient buy-in, resistance to change, and skill deficits are all challenges that will be faced by the incumbent in this position.

